  "doc_id": "prion_0372",
  "text": "Creutzfeldt-Jakob disease (CJD) surveillance relies on autopsy and neuropathologic evaluation.\nThe 1990-2000 CJD autopsy rate in California was 21%.\nMost neurologists were comfortable diagnosing CJD (83%), but few pathologists felt comfortable diagnosing CJD (35%) or performing autopsy (29%).\nAddressing obstacles to autopsy is necessary to improve CJD surveillance.",
